spanGrp.span: _ axun migouba, n mexanys xwerawdad, ekas anqd migo uba i latxwarte ad orte.
_ Once my uncle, when we were on the Mekhana mountain, then my uncle went off to go hunting in the rocks.
_ ertxel biaemi ("emi biia"), ven rom mexanas ("mexanais[a]s") mtai viqavit ("vearvebodit"), main adga ("movida"<v. k. "moqda") biaemi ("emi biia") da sanadirod (dr. v. k. "txevla") cavida ldeebisen.

nina gueiani (odoris xeobis svanuri enis balskvemouri dialekis carmomadgeneli); ketevan margiani (odoris xeobis svanuri enis balszemouri dialekis carmomadgeneli); vova gueiani. rogor caales apxazebma kartvelebis vali gamokvabuli.

Speakers: Nina Gujejiani (LB-Kodori); Vova Gujejiani (LB-Kodori); interviewer: Ketevan Margiani (UB-Kodori). How the Abkhaz people swept off the Georgians' trail. Video 18; (0:05:03:760 _ 0:10:34.400).
im' axirx apxzrd kartelre l gamokabulisga.
He was a good hunter man.
He went there and he saw some game animals.
cavida da naxa turme ("daunaxavs") nadirebi ("na[sa]txevlarebs", dr. v. k. "txevla").
exu lmr rel, e rels er axtope i k'anqd, xaqid bgid sarxal.
One of them was motley, when he fired at that motley animal and caused it to fall, a big hail began.
erti qopila reli, im rels rom esrola ("a-top-a") da gadmovarda, dauva ("daarqa") magari ("magrad"<v. k. "brge-d") seqva.
morublul deme lsw, ei sarxal xaqid i al sarxalxenka ali tawesapars xetxelida.
The sky was cloudless, (yet) so the hail began, and he was looking for a shelter from this hail.
morubluli ar iqo, ise dauva ("daarqa") seqva da am seqvisgan es tavesapars eebda (dr. v. k. "txevla").
Wherever he came, it poured upon him.
tawesapars er xetxelida, gamonaxa exu dgilas.
When he was looking for shelter he found one place.
tavesapars rom eebda (dr. v. k. "txevl-a"), gamonaxa ert adgilas.
axw dgis gamokwabulal lsw i eeu imi pardul, ami gadmoparebul lsw.
At (this) one place, there was something like a cave and there, like a barn, so he was sheltered.
ert adgilas gamokvabulivit iqo da ik rogorc parduli, ase iqo gadmoparebuli.
He laid down under it and looked upside.
amis kve dacva da uqurebs zemot.
xawsmodebuls uka xecd carceras, al carceras xecd i anqd i k'atxne al carcera.
Covered under the moss, he saw an inscription, he inspected this inscription and started to scrape this inscription off.
xavsmodebuls kvemot dainaxa carcera ("carceras"), am carceras exeda da adga ("movida", v. k. "mo-qd-a") da gadapxia es carcera.
eeu dwed, ere: al laxws eser lmrdeli atsiarairi... isa..., atsiarairiigwid, igwided... ei.., mu... muwabrer de uli.
There he read that: "In this mountain in one thousand eight hundred and... umm... in one thousand eight hundred and seven, seventy..." umm... I cannot say it in the Lower-Bal dialect.
ik caiitxa, rom: am mtai ("mtaso") qopilao ("namqopa") atasrvaas da... isa..., atasrvaasvid ("atas-i-da-rva-as-i-da-vid-i"), samocdaati (vididaati")... isa..., balskvemourad ver vambob.
_ Speak in the Lower-Bal dialect, in the Lower-Bal dialect!
_ Yes, I can't say it, and...
_ Say it in what ever way you can say it.
_ igwidedexw zawi lmrd mix... mixyl waracxelia ameu.
_ "In the year one thousand eight hundred and seventy-one Mikha... Mikhail Kvaratskhelia was here."
_ samocdatertme ("vidiatiert") cels ("celi") qopila ("namqopa") mixa... mixail varacxelia ak.
alr mg aninul wacwir ameu i...
es ("eseni") qvelaperi ("qvela") aninuli daova ak da...
_ anqdx apxzr i {samocda...} igwidedisami, obaxyol, samocdatormei xom daaqenes?
_ The Abkhaz people came and in (the year) {sixty...} seventy-three, the Kobakhias, in seventy-two they had (that place) settled (there), right?
_ movidnen apxazebi da {samocda...} samocdacamei ("vidiatidasam[s]ze"), obaxiebi samocdatormei xom daaqenes?
_ wo, samocdatormei daaqenes i ekanwe igwidedisami {iswenebda} mia weraliow gwandr laxws i mi i migu biawil i migomu al gwandr laxws, mindors, ere mznnid xwardad.

_ Yes, they did so in seventy-two, and then in seventy-three he rested (there) with his helicopter in the Gvandra mountain and me and my cousin and my poor father, on the Gvandra mountain, and me and my cousin and my poor father, we were there, on the Gvandra mountain, in the field, to attend them.

_ ho, samocdatormei daaqenes da mere samocdacamei ("vidiatidasam[s]ze") {isvenebda} tavisi vemprenit ("veralioit") gvandri[s] mtai ("mtas") da me da emi biavili da sacqali mamaemi ("emi mama") gvandris mtai ("mta-s"), mindori ("mindor-s"), mat ("imeebi[s]"<"e-g-i-eb-i-[s]") momvlelad ("mzrunvel[a]d") viqavit ("vimqopebodit").
exu ninlew oxqd sirdon gueians apxzrcaxn.
Once Spiriton Gujejiani had a bet with the Abkhaz people.
ertxel ("erti") danilaveba mouxda ("mouqda") siridon gueians apxazebtan.
apxzrd rkwex: _ "mine rok li al xeoba tawidan", _ i k'xnirzal sirdon gueian mypxzi wicinias.
The Abkhaz people said, "this canyon has been ours from the beginning", and Spiridon Gujejian had a bet with the Abkhaz (man) Kvitsinia.
apxazebma tkves: _ "veniao es xeoba tavidanve ("tavidan")", _ da daenilava siridon gueiani apxaz vicinias.
He had a bet with Kvitsinia.
Because of this bet they rode up with (their) horses.
'adx i wadmicawex, ere apxzr sgebd eeu lmr ei, al laxwr, waracxelyole, zanre.
They rode up and proved that before the Abkhaz people (came), these mountains there had belonged to the Kvaratskhelias, Megrelian people.
avidnen da daamices, rom apxazebamde ("apxazebi[s] cin") ik es mtebi qopila varacxeliebis, megrelebis ("zan-eb-i[s]").
_ ekano wanxx i al linlew caago e mypxzid i mypxzi xakwrida sirdon gueians, biaems, liwers i exu cin aronrs, mare amnem mad nid:
_ Then they returned and this Abkhaz man had lost this bet and the Abkhaz man was to give Spiridon Gujejian, my uncle, a revolver and one basket of cartridges, but he refused this, (saying):
_ mere dabrundnen ("amobrundnen") da es nilavi caago im apxazma da apxazi uknida siridon gueians, biaems, revolvers da ert alata qviebs, magram aman ar gamoartva ("aio"<"aiida"):
"alr rok sabolood demeg lix bgid sando", _ demeg xbida.
"They are not very trustworthy, after all," (so) he didn't accept it.
"eseni ("esenio") sabolood ar ariano alian ("magrad"< v. k. "brge-d") sando", _ ar gamoartva ("caartva").

_ ekano anqd weralio, lim... {wocdacxra agwisos}, yerwedixara agwisos weralio anqd i al weraliow esrdax apxzr, ekas n er bgid oxznaned alrs, obaxias i mia xlxs, ea, obaxias xuwanda silos wlis, walxenka, iwxenka msqe... mde..., nard, ali lanukwre.

_ Then a helicopter came... {on August 29th,} it came on August 29th and the Abkhaz people were in this helicopter, (and) then we attended them so well, look, Kobakhia and his people, therefore - he had a backgammon game made from ivory, from ivory, ivory, that he gave me as a gift.

_ mere movida (dr. v. k. "qdoma") vempreni ("veralioi")... {ocdacxra agvisos,} ocdacxra agvisos vempreni ("veralioi") movida (dr. v. k. "qdoma") da am vemprenit ("veralioit") midiodnen apxazebi, main ven rom argad ("magrad"< v. k. "brge-d") movuaret ("vumzrunvelet") amat ("eseebs"), ai, obaxias i mis xalxs, imiom ("imistvis"), obaxias hkonda silos vlis, vlisgan, vlisgan gaetebuli... isa..., nardi, es gvauka.
ali, anqd migu... migouba sirdon i:
He, my uncle Sriridon, stood up and (said):
es, adga ("movida", dr. v. k. "qdoma") biaemi ("emi biia") siridoni da:

"alr rok lmxl xlx lix i eys rok ka xaulix gwige ryomisga i raiamasomisga i saminisroisga, ere kira rok anidx apxzrd rok, eis xaulix, ere n, dinol, er xoznnidad, ama rok kira anidx", _ i oma werlio 'nmrtawn, sirdond al nard 'owr etei i ei n anxrnda i xyr xwaqd migoubas, ere "alr rok alis daaqwedreben rok guge xlxs, ryoms rok i ers".

"They are wicked people," (he said), "they will tell our regional party committee and the executive committee and the ministry that we made them pay a rent, the Abkhaz people, they would say, that: "We, the girls were nursing them and that's why they made us pay the rent," - and when the helicopter started, Spiridon threw this backgammon up in to that (helicopter), and we were very sad (about) that, and I almost beat my uncle, (saying) that "they will reproach our people because of this at the regional committee."

"eseni ("esenio") emai ("mcodne") xalxi ariano da imas ("imaso") eqviano vens raiomi da raiamasomi da saminisroi, rom kira gadagvaxdevineso apxazebma ("apxazebmao"), imas eqvian, rom (raxan) ven, gogoebi, vuvlidit, amiom ("amistvis") kira gadagvaxdevineso ("gamogvartves")", _ da rodesac ("roca") vempreni ("veralioi") airto ("moimarta"), siridonma es nardi augdo imaze da is ven gvecqina da inaam davarqi biaems ("ems biias"), rom "eseni ("esenio") amas daaqvedrebeno vens xalxs, raioms ("raiomso") da imat ("imeebs").
_ "They will demand a recompense," yes, and... then they left.
e zaw mama, odd merma zaw ibe laxwrte.
That year, no, the next year we went into the upper mountains.
im cels ara (da), cavedit meore cels zeda mtebi ("mteb{is}en").
'otixd mexyl laxwte i ad migouba e gamokwabuli lasnwite i anx u nebozs i turme m xowminax mine xlxs!
We turned up towards the Mekhaili mountain and my uncle went to inspect that cave and he returned in the evening and what had those people done!
aviqvanet ("avabrunet") mexailis mtai da cavida biaemi ("emi biia") im gamokvabulis dasatvaliereblad ("gasasinad") da dabrunda ("amobrunda") saamos da turme ra uknia ("ukniat") mat xalxs!
They had blasted it entirely with explosives.
Nothing was visible there at all.
araperi ("ara sakme") ar anda ik saertod.
That is, they had swept it off.
_ They had swept off the trail of the Megrelians.
_ aha, i isgwa buba nxirnnma i?
_ Aha, and did your uncle get angry?
_ i sgy mngwemo wemind atxe, merawad.
_ And we couldn't do anything now, being in the mountains.
_ da tkven veraperi ver kenit axla, mtai mqopebma ("moarveebma").
ei mtlynd o imido axxwirx ami ka, gun mamba.
How could they destroy the whole rock, I was very surprised.
is lde mtlianad ase rogor gamoangries, alian ("gulad") mivirs.
That is, they had lost the bet...
_ i amno e wali caales, xosdima?!
_ And that's why (lit. with that) they swept off that trail, you see?
_ da amit is vali caales, xedav?!
_ ik carcera rom iqo, is upro gwian tkwa.
_ That there was the inscription, that he said (only) later..
_ ik carcera rom iqo, is upro gvian tkva.
e carcera xo caiitxa biaemma da einem, inem ub er rkwe, mi amacerina bubad.
After my uncle had read that inscription and he, when he told (about) it down (here), my uncle made me write the inscription down.
is carcera xom caiitxa biaemma da iman, tviton kvemot rom tkva, me amacerina biiam.
ali amacerina i e carcerad xoil gwyand min lmrdx wocdarwa clit, yerwediara zaww xoil gwyand lmrdx apxzr amelea zanrd.

He made me write this down, and before this inscription (was made) they had been there themselves for twenty-eight years, before the Megrelians (came there), the Abkhaz were there twenty-eight years later.
es amacerina da im carceramde upro gvian tviton qopilan ("namqopan") ocdarva clit, megrelebamde ("zanebamde") ocdarva clit upro gvian qopilan ("namqopan") apxazebi ak ("am{is} zemot").
al daceril... ei..., solsapr uk' mdwne.
This note... umm... he made me put this under the table-cloth.
es dacerili... isa..., magidis gadasapareblis ("solsapari") kve damadebina.
oma wanqdx wicinia i i arw, ekas einem rkwe.
When Kvitsinia and he himself arrived on (their) horses, then he said it.
rodesac amovidnen (v. k. "ta-mo-qd-en") vicinia da tviton cxenebit, main iman tkva.
"nu, wen cawag... n rok, cawaget rok n, cawaget", _ i k'amqidne buba sirdond i ka loxce i yerwediara z gansxwaweba lsw uxwarnensga.
"Well, we've los... we, we've lost, we've lost," and uncle Spiridon made me take it out and I showed it to them and the difference between the two events (lit. one another) was twenty-eight years.
"nu, ven cavag... veno, cavageto ven, cavaget", _ da gamomaanina biia siridonma da vavene da ertmanets oris ocdarva ("oriatidarva") celi iqo gansxvaveba.
_ ameld zaw xoni lmrdx zanr amelea.
_ So many years earlier the Megrelians had been there.
_ amdeni ("am raodenoba") clit adre qopilan megrelebi ("zan-eb-i") ak ("am{is} zemot").
_ aha, i mdebareoba imi xuwn gwandr laxws?
_ Aha, and what location did the Gvandra mountain have?
_ aha, da mdebareoba rogori hkonda gvandris mtas?
ube laxw, mindwers er xwaulid, ei li na.
The Lower mountain, which we call the 'field', that is a plain.
kveda mta, mindors rom veaxit, is aris vae.
ibe laxwr, er, i lezi lix ori masrd i ib dirr, mare mtagoryn lix mege.
The Upper mountains, they, (to get there) you must climb up the rocks, and there are plains up there, but they are very, very mountainous places.
zeda mtebi, isini, asasvlelia ("arian") ldeebze namenavad da zemot vaeebia ("vaeebi"), magram alian ("magari") mtagoriania ("arian").
_ i xed tanr... mde... girid eas... xacxi?
_ And which passes... umm... around that... are there?
_ da romeli uelexilebi... isa... irgvliv imas... arqia?
_ i e g{w}andary tanw imte li ka lz qrateya?
_ And where do you get through that Gvandra pass, to Kabardia-Balkaria?
_ da im ("is") gvandaris uelexilit sait aris gadasasvleli ("gasasvleli") qabardo-balqareti ("qaraa-et-[s]-en?")?
